09/11/2021,748.303(a)(3)(A) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,12/23/2021,04/28/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Operation failed to timely report allegations of abuse to a child.  ,"04/28/2023- The Executive Director submitted the operation's Corrective Action Plan consisting of ensuring the operation will respond to allegations of serious incidents of Abuse and Neglect according to the operation's Reporting Serious Incidents, Abuse and Neglect Allegations Policy. The operation will ensure that any abuse or neglect allegations will be reported to the Texas Hotline immediately but no later than 24 hours. The operation will also ensure that all Serious Incidents, Abuse and Neglect allegations are reported via email or phone call to the assigned DFPS Residential Contract Manager and assigned Residential Child Care Licensing Rep within 24 hours of being notified of such an occurrence. 

The operation's Case Manager will be responsible for notification of DFPS Contract Manager. The Executive Director will be responsible for notifying the assigned licensing representative.
 
The operation will continue to require all employees to complete pre-service and annual trainings regarding reporting Serious Incidents, Abuse and Neglect and will conduct an additional refresher course for all employees to be completed within 30 days of this date (02/22/2022). 

According to the Executive Director, on January 31st, 2022, a broadcast MEMO document was sent to all of the operation's employees to notify them of the Abuse/Neglect refresher training scheduled for February 2022. The scheduled dates for trainings were 02/08/2022,02/10/2022, and 2/19/2022. 

The operation's Administrative Assistant currently provides oversight and ensures compliance with trainings by performing quarterly audits and will continue in that capacity. The Administrative Assistant will be listed as the Training Coordinator and will ensure that all trainers utilized by the operation to facilitate this training on Reporting Serious Incidents, Abuse and Neglect who are selected provide through signature their title and name at the time of training.

The operation's Licensed Child Care Administrator will ensure that all serious Incidents, Abuse/Neglect are reported timely and will be reported to the Residential Contract Manager.

At the conclusion of the trainings that are scheduled, the operation's Executive Director will submit proof of training for all staff, case managers and caregivers on reporting Serious Incidents, Abuse and Neglect. The documentation will include training certificates along with the participants' signature. 
"
